               <font>
                  <Font name="Lucida Console" size="12.0" />
               </font>
               <VBox.margin>
                  <Insets bottom="30.0" left="30.0" right="30.0" top="30.0" />
               </VBox.margin>
            </Text>
            <Text fill="WHITE" layoutX="23.0" layoutY="39.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="So the 755 covers permissions for all the groups at once. The first number is your user, the second number is for your group, and 5 is other permissions.&#10;&#10;7 and 5 aren't on the list I hear you ask, well you have to add up the 3 numbers to work out the permissions. &#10;&#10;4+2+1 = 7, so the user has all permissions, 4+1 = 5, so the Group has read and execute permissions, and same again for Other permissions." wrappingWidth="456.0">
